<TEXT>
voters in this denver suburb on 
tuesday recalled their mayor and four city council members in a flap 
that began when a tv crew filmed the police and fire chiefs drinking 
on the job 
the mayor condoned the activity said recall organizer verna 
cook as far as the council is concerned i certainly think that 
their inaction has caused his to happen and they should be 
recalled 
voters cast 801 ballots to recall mayor lester bauer 81 and 361 
to retain him said city clerk peggy french mark stickel was 
elected his successor with 433 votes 
four of the councils six members were recalled mildred early 
bob hamilton grace diamond and mayor pro tem ernest shelton french 
said they were replaced by richard wright robert snell linda dunn 
and al pfluger council incumbents wayne martin and early headly 
held onto their seats 
cook herself ran for mayor to unseat bauer who in november 
survived another recall vote she spearheaded over skunk removal 
tuesdays recall election stemmed from a series of reports on 
denvers kusatv in april in which police chief dwain farris and 
fire chief jim fyffe were filmed drinking at bars while on duty on 
several afternoons 
the city council initially asked for farris resignation and 
suspended fyffe for 30 days without pay but an angry crowd at a 
city council meeting the next night persuaded the council to fire 
both men 
cook said that the council knew about the mens alleged drinking 
problems before the televised reports but did nothing about them 
she then organized the recall drive against bauer and the four 
council members ousted tuesday 
shelton who was targeted in the recall started a recall effort 
of his own against martin and headly who survived tuesdays 
election 
bauer said of cooks second recall campaign she has that right 
and thats her prerogative thats twice that theyve tried it but 
i think shell have a big job on her hands to recall the entire 
council 
french had said she expected good turnout among the 4500 
registered voters but turnout was light fifteen candidates vied 
for seven seats voters decided first whether to recall the 
incumbents and then who should replace them 
in the recall election in november ballots were counted three 
times before it was determined that bauer had kept his job by one 
vote 896895 
that recall was launched after a resident was cited for shooting 
a skunk bauer opponents rallied around the resident saying the 
city had stopped paying for removal of stray animals 
</TEXT>
