eastern airlines ranks high in ontime 
performance but also leads the industry in complaints from 
consumers according to a transportation department monthly report 
the departments air travel consumer report released monday 
showed eastern with 1310 complaints to the government per 100000 
passengers more than twice the rate of any other airline 
the figures do not cover complaints made directly to the airlines 
but only those received by the government 
pan american was second with 602 complaints per 100000 fliers 
followed by trans world airlines with 459 at the bottom of the 
list of 21 airlines were aloha and tower airlines with no complaints 
the report covers a wide variety of consumer complaints 
including problems with fares overbooking baggage handling 
customer service advertising and smoking on flights 
in the category for lost or mishandled baggage eastern had the 
lowest number of reports 267 per 1000 passengers in may the 
reports on baggage and the flight performance were for may and 
overall consumer complaints to the government covered june 
the report cautions that the baggage statistics are based on 
reports from the airlines and may not be comparable because carriers 
have differing methods of reporting 
the report showed america west leading in ontime performance 
with 917 percent of its flights arriving on time in may followed 
by eastern with 872 percent and alaska airlines with 87 percent 
the report noted however that the eastern statistics covered far 
fewer flights than normal because of the ongoing walkout by the 
airlines machinists union which has been joined by pilots and 
flight attendants 
