a moderate earthquake shook several 
northern california communities but no damage was reported 
the tremor which measured 45 on the richter scale struck at 
915 pm monday and was centered about 10 miles west of bishop the 
us geological society said 
it rolled said pam galvin of the bishop police department 
i was standing up doing some work and i felt the ground roll under 
me it was really bizarre ive never felt one like that before 
it also was felt 120 miles to the west in fresno and in mammouth 
lakes 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight damage 
in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 
