be lifted when things have completely returned to normal and when 
we feel that all the problems of the rebellion that need to be 
resolved have been 
he said sanctions imposed by some western countries to protest 
the crackdown will cause some temporary trouble for chinas 
ailing economy among the problems are inflation that yuan said was 
running at 255 percent in the first half of the year and growing 
budget and trade deficits 
but the chinese people will not yield to these pressures 
because of these troubles he said on the contrary it will 
inspire a spirit of plain living and hard struggle and relying on 
our own efforts so in the long run it will do our country good 
yuan refused to disclose figures for the number of people 
arrested since the crackdown began the associated press has counted 
