when driving in fog at night should your cars 
headlights be set on high beam or low beam 
the answer is low beam which will direct light onto the road 
ahead while light from high beams will hit the fog and be reflected 
that question and answer were part of a practice test released 
tuesday to prepare motorists for the national driving test on aug 
29 on cbs just before the long labor day weekend 
more people lose their lives in accidents during the labor day 
holiday than any other holiday period 
its been a long time since most of us took a driving test 
