bill would compromise the anonymity of foreign firms reporting 
information to the us government and discourage foreign 
investment which the administration welcomes because it helps 
modernize us industry 
enactment of this proposal would ultimately increase the cost 
of capital in the us and result in slower economic growth weaker 
productivity performance lower rates of employment and american 
products which are less competitive in world markets he said 
darby said the administration prefers with some adjustments a 
bill sponsored by sen frank h murkowski ralaska which imposes 
