headquarters agency spokesman robert nipp said monday 
the four were placed on 30day administrative leave at the start 
of the investigation last month that period expired monday and hud 
officials decided to give the four 90day temporary assignments as 
the investigation continues 
an audit of the washington field office uncovered lax financial 
and management controls that allowed private closing agents hired by 
hud to handle singlefamily property to delay payments to the 
government and in some cases not make them at all 
