limiting outside income for top city officials but not before some 
council members slammed the bill as a thinly veiled attempt to 
discourage jesse jackson from running for mayor 
the bill proposed by mayoral hopeful john ray a member of the 
council limits the outside income for the mayor and council members 
to 10000 per year 
another candidate for mayor council chairman david clarke 
succeeded in attaching an amendment that sets a 10000 annual limit 
for royalty earnings by the mayor and council chairman 
jackson whose advisors have said he is strongly considering 
running for mayor in 1990 was traveling in egypt and could not be 
reached for comment 
the mayors job pays 82500 a year 
one council member called the bill a cheap shot at jackson 
who earns most of his 200000 annual income from giving speeches 
i think it looks like a cheap shot and we always look foolish 
when it looks like were trying to keep someone from running said 
frank smith it usually turns out to be a shortsighted mistake 
