these are some of the key developments in the 
takeover battle surrounding time inc 
nov 10 1988 time chairman j richard munro hinting at plans 
for an acquisition or merger tells securities analysts time intends 
to become a global media conglomerate 
march 4 1989 time and warner communications inc announce they 
will merge in a friendly stock swap to form time warner inc the 
worlds largest communications concern 
april 9 gulf amp western inc says it put its consumer finance 
segment the associates up for sale allowing the company to focus 
on its entertainment and publishing businesses gulf amp western says 
