<TEXT>
digital equipment corp introduced a wide range of 
new computers tuesday including several based on reduced 
instruction set computing technology rather than digitals 
traditional vax design 
the new products are aimed at strengthening digital in the market 
for powerful workstations used by engineers scientists and 
designers digital is the nations second largest computer maker 
behind international business machines corp 
reduced instruction set computing or risc simplifies the 
circuitry of a computers central processor and offers cost savings 
but it is a new thrust for digital which until this year built all 
its machines around its proprietary vax architecture 
among the maynardbased companys new offerings is its decstation 
2100 a workstation using a risc microprocessor made by mips 
computer co of sunnyvale calif and the unix operating system 
developed by american telephone amp telegraph co 
digital said the machine with a price tag starting at 7950 is 
the industrys lowestpriced color riscbased unix workstation 
digital also announced several new entries in its vax line led 
by the vax 6400 which it said is up to 85 percent more powerful 
than its previous highend machine the vax 8840 
a new version of the vms operating system software for vax 
machines was also introduced digital said it would more than double 
the number of computers that can be clustered in a vax network from 
42 to 96 
