<TEXT>
delta air lines decision to establish an employee 
stock ownership plan is being widely viewed as a deterrent to 
unwanted suitors at a time when takeover speculation has swept 
through the airline business 
nwa inc the minneapolis parent of northwest airlines recently 
was the subject of a takeover battle chicagobased ual corp the 
parent of united airlines has been the subject of recent media and 
wall street speculation that it might be targeted for acquisition 
and atlantas delta has been mentioned often in recent months as an 
attractive candidate for a takeover 
delta the nations third largest carrier generally does not 
comment on such speculation officials said the esop announced 
monday was not intended as a guard against a takeover 
we prefer to focus on the business aspect of the move as far 
as the esop it brings more in line the employee interest and the 
shareholder interest delta spokesman jim lundy said tuesday it 
gives the employees a much bigger stake in the company 
lundy said he was not aware of any other major airlines having 
esops but he noted employee stock ownership has become increasingly 
common throughout us industry 
deltas move which came the same day as an announcement of a 25 
millionshare stock sale to swissair was seen by some analysts as 
an attempt to erect a barrier to anyone considering a hostile 
takeover of the airline 
they noted that the esop combined with the swissair purchase 
would put 19 percent of the companys stock in friendly hands 
in trading tuesday on the new york stock exchange delta fell 50 
cents a share to 7125 
robert j joedicke an analyst with shearson lehman brothers inc 
in new york said deltas actions appeared to be wise 
i think its a prudent move with that possible takeovers in 
mind joedicke said a company nwa with similar 
characteristics just went through the same takeover situation 
you cant establish these things after you get a phone call 
saying were going to make a bid for you 
joedicke said esops are a sign of the times in an age of 
corporate raiders and debtfinanced buyouts of large corporations 
he said airlines are as likely as any to spark the interest of 
takeover artists airlines assets particularly their valuable 
fleets of jets make them especially attractive 
they takeovers tend to go through industries joedicke 
said food was great with beatrice and rjr nabisco when they 
finish running through that industry theyve got to look elsewhere 
for likely candidates 
paul p karos an airline industry analyst with first boston 
corp said esops have the added benefit of solidifying the loyalty 
of the workforce 
it has a motivating effect on the employees and it gives them 
incentive to do a good job karos said 
under the delta esop nearly 7 million shares of delta preferred 
stock were purchased for about 500 million the shares will be 
allocated to employees in lieu of existing cash contributions to the 
plan but they can be converted into common stock shares worth 
8640 each 
the preferred stock will pay 6 percent a year in dividends 
the swissair deal called for the sale of 25 million shares of 
delta common stock to the swiss carrier for 1933 million or about 
77 a share the agreement includes a reciprocal purchase by delta 
of up to 100000 or 5 percent of swissairs shares 
the two airlines agreed in march to develop joint operating and 
marketing agreements 
